170,700 BARRELS OF OIL AND 467 MILLION CUBIC FEET OF

NATURAL GAS DURING 2002. THIS INCLUDES THE ALBA FIELD IN THE

UNITED KINGDOM NORTH SEA, WHERE CHEVRONTEXACO IS OPERATOR AND

HOLDS A 21 PERCENT EQUITY INTEREST, WHICH HAD TOTAL DAILY

PRODUCTION OF 61,200 BARRELS OF CRUDE OIL AND

11 MILLION CUBIC FEET OF NATURAL GAS. THE ALBA EXTREME

SOUTH PROJECT ACHIEVED FIRST OIL PRODUCTION IN OCTOBER 2002,

